<!-- FAQ Section -->
<section class="faq-section" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-tag">FAQ</span>
      <h2>Common Questions</h2>
      <p>Find quick answers about our roadmaps and contribution process.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="faq-accordion-container">
      
      <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-question-text">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-sparkles faq-q-icon"></i>
            What makes CampusCompass unique?
          </span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down faq-chevron"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Unlike other platforms, CampusCompass does not use AI recommendations. It relies on curated, peer-vetted static JSON roadmaps. This ensures the curriculum is focused, structured, and free of AI hallucinations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-question-text">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-square-poll-vertical faq-q-icon"></i>
            How does the progress tracker match my skills?
          </span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down faq-chevron"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>The dashboard reads the skill tags on your profile. It performs a case-insensitive search matching those tag strings against the topic names and descriptions in your roadmap. When matches are found, it checks them off and recalculates your overall progress.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
  
      <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-question-text">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-database faq-q-icon"></i>
            Is the database completely offline?
          </span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down faq-chevron"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. The project uses a local, lightweight file database (`data/users.json`). There are no external database cloud logins or local database servers required, meaning you can boot and develop the project 100% offline.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
  
      <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span class="faq-question-text">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-code-fork faq-q-icon"></i>
            Can I contribute a new career roadmap?
          </span>
          <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down faq-chevron"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Absolutely! We welcome student contributions, particularly during open-source events. You can create a new career JSON file (e.g., `mobile-developer.json`) under `data/roadmaps/` and add it to our config files. Read our `CONTRIBUTING.md` file for details.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

